data.enText: a device in a wall that you put a plug into in order to connect electrical equipment to the power supply of a building
a device on a piece of electrical equipment that you can fix a plug, a light bulb , etc. into
an aerial socket on the television
a curved hollow space in the surface of sth that another part fits into or moves around in

data.chText: 他的两眼从眼窝里鼓出来。
data.enText: His eyes bulged in their sockets.

tr: a receptacle into which an electric device can be inserted
receptacle where something (a pipe or probe or end of a bone) is inserted
a bony hollow into which a structure fits

value.def: A socket is a device on a piece of electrical equipment into which you can put a bulb or plug.
A socket is a device or point in a wall where you can connect electrical equipment to the power supply.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 outlet

value.def: You can refer to any hollow part or opening in a structure which another part fits into as a socket .

example.ex: Rotate the shoulders in their sockets five times...
example.tran: 让肩膀绕臼部转动 5 次。

example.ex: Her eyes were sunk deep into their sockets.
example.tran: 她的眼睛深陷在眼窝里。
